    {
      "id": "cultural_w3",
      "type": "cultural_note",
      "title": "Kulturelt hjørne — Families in Denmark",
      "content": "Danish families come in many shapes and sizes. Denmark has one of the world's highest rates of children born outside of marriage — over half of all children are born to unmarried parents, though many live in stable partnerships ('papirløst samlevende'). The word 'kæreste' is gender-neutral and means boyfriend, girlfriend, or partner. Note also that Danish distinguishes which side of the family a grandparent comes from: 'farmor' is your father's mother, 'mormor' is your mother's mother, 'farfar' is your father's father, and 'morfar' is your mother's father. When speaking to Danes, using first names is the norm — even with teachers and older relatives."
